# llamaseye — example environment file
#
# Copy this to .env and source it before running llamaseye, or export
# variables individually in your shell profile.
#
#   cp example.env .env
#   source .env && bash llamaseye.sh --models-dir ~/Models
#
# Every variable has a built-in default — only set the ones you want to override.
# All of these can also be passed as CLI flags (see --help).

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Binaries
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Path to your llama-bench binary (built from llama.cpp).
# Must be compiled with the right backend flags for your hardware.
# See README.md > Dependencies for build instructions.
# Required — no default. Example:
# LLAMA_BENCH_BIN="${HOME}/llama.cpp/build/bin/llama-bench"

# Path to a TurboQuant llama-bench binary (optional).
# Enables turbo2/turbo3/turbo4 KV cache types.
# Built from: github.com/TheTom/llama-cpp-turboquant (branch: feature/turboquant-kv-cache)
# Leave unset to disable TurboQuant sweeps entirely.
# SWEEP_TURBO_BENCH_BIN="${HOME}/llama-cpp-turboquant/build/bin/llama-bench"

# Path to a RotorQuant llama-bench binary (optional).
# [EXPERIMENTAL - currently broken, do not use]
# Enables planar3/planar4/iso3/iso4 KV cache types.
# Built from: github.com/johndpope/llama-cpp-turboquant (branch: feature/planarquant-kv-cache)
# Leave unset to disable RotorQuant sweeps entirely.
# SWEEP_ROTOR_BENCH_BIN="${HOME}/llama-cpp-rotorquant/build/bin/llama-bench"

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Model & output paths
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Directory to scan for .gguf model files when no --model flag is given.
# No default — set this to wherever your .gguf files live. Example:
# SWEEP_MODELS_DIR="${HOME}/Models"

# Root directory where sweep results are written.
# Each model gets its own subdirectory: <SWEEP_OUTPUT_DIR>/<model-stem>/
# Defaults to ./results (relative to wherever you run the script).
# SWEEP_OUTPUT_DIR="./results"

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sweep behaviour
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Step size for the NGL (GPU layer) axis sweep.
# Smaller = finer resolution, longer runtime. Reduce to 2 for models near the VRAM edge.
SWEEP_NGL_STEP=4

# Number of repetitions per benchmark run (-r passed to llama-bench).
# Higher = more stable results. Lower = faster sweeps.
SWEEP_REPETITIONS=3

# Repetitions used during the Phase 0 NGL probe (speed doesn'''t matter here, just load success).
SWEEP_PROBE_REPS=1

# Per-run timeout in seconds. Runs exceeding this are killed and recorded as timed out.
SWEEP_TIMEOUT_SEC=600

# Minimum TG tokens/sec to consider a config viable for interactive use.
# Configs below this threshold are still recorded but marked viable=false.
SWEEP_MIN_TG_TS=2.0

# Seconds to wait between runs (passed as --delay to llama-bench).
# Gives a lightweight cooldown between short runs.
SWEEP_DELAY_SEC=5

# llama-bench process priority (--prio). 0=normal 1=medium 2=high 3=realtime.
SWEEP_PRIO=2

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Thermal limits
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CPU temperature ceiling in °C. The sweep pauses if this is exceeded.
# Set slightly below your CPU's hard thermal limit.
SWEEP_CPU_TEMP_LIMIT=88

# GPU temperature ceiling in °C. The sweep pauses if this is exceeded.
SWEEP_GPU_TEMP_LIMIT=81

# Seconds between thermal polls while waiting to cool down.
SWEEP_COOL_POLL_SEC=20

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Execution control
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Resume a previous sweep, skipping already-completed phases.
# Equivalent to --resume. Set to "true" to enable.
# SWEEP_RESUME=false

# Delete existing output dir before starting. Equivalent to --overwrite.
# SWEEP_OVERWRITE=false

# Print bench commands without executing them. Equivalent to --dry-run.
# SWEEP_DRY_RUN=false

# Skip the pre-sweep confirmation prompt. Equivalent to --no-confirm.
# SWEEP_NO_CONFIRM=false

# Disable thermal polling entirely. Equivalent to --no-thermal-guard.
# SWEEP_NO_THERMAL=false

# Run only these phases (comma-separated). Equivalent to --only-phases.
# SWEEP_ONLY_PHASES=0,1,2

# Skip these phases (comma-separated). Equivalent to --skip-phases.
# SWEEP_SKIP_PHASES=7

# Only run combos not already in sweep.jsonl. Equivalent to --focused.
# Requires --only-phases. Skipped combos still populate working sets for downstream phases.
# SWEEP_FOCUSED=false

# Path to a model list file (one filename per line). Equivalent to --model-list.
# SWEEP_MODEL_LIST=~/bench_list.txt

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Axis start points
# Each axis sweep begins at the start of its list by default.
# Set these to skip ahead — useful when the low end has already been explored
# or is known to be uninteresting.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Begin the NGL sweep at this value instead of 0. Equivalent to --start-ngl.
# SWEEP_START_NGL=40

# Begin the thread-count sweep at this value. Equivalent to --start-threads.
# SWEEP_START_THREADS=8

# Begin the context sweep at this prompt size. Equivalent to --start-ctx.
# Useful to skip sub-32k contexts: SWEEP_START_CTX=32768
# SWEEP_START_CTX=32768

# Begin the KV quant sweep at this type. Equivalent to --start-ctk.
# Ordering (up = more compression): f16 q8_0 q4_0 turbo4 turbo3 turbo2
# SWEEP_START_CTK=q8_0

# Begin the V-cache quant sweep at this type. Equivalent to --start-ctv.
# Same ordering as CTK. Ignored when SWEEP_CTV is set.
# SWEEP_START_CTV=q8_0

# Restrict Phase 2 to only these V-cache types (comma-separated). Equivalent to --ctv.
# Takes precedence over SWEEP_START_CTV and SWEEP_CTV_DIR.
# SWEEP_CTV=turbo3,turbo2

# Begin the batch sweep at this value. Equivalent to --start-b.
# SWEEP_START_B=512

# Begin the ubatch sweep at this value. Equivalent to --start-ub.
# SWEEP_START_UB=128

# Begin the FA sweep at this value (0=off, 1=on). Equivalent to --start-fa.
# SWEEP_START_FA=0

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Axis sweep directions
# "up" = sweep from start toward the high end of the list (default for all axes).
# "down" = sweep from start toward the low end.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# SWEEP_NGL_DIR=up
# SWEEP_THREADS_DIR=up
# SWEEP_CTX_DIR=up
# SWEEP_CTK_DIR=up
# SWEEP_CTV_DIR=up
# SWEEP_B_DIR=up
# SWEEP_UB_DIR=up
# SWEEP_FA_DIR=up

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Phase 7 minimum thresholds
# These filter the combination matrix inputs. Phases 1–6 still run full
# discovery; only Phase 7 is narrowed. For numeric axes, values strictly
# below the minimum are excluded. For ctk, types below the minimum in
# quality order are excluded.
# KV quality order (low->high): turbo2 turbo3 turbo4 q4_0 q8_0 f16
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Exclude NGL values below N from Phase 7. Equivalent to --min-ngl.
# SWEEP_MIN_NGL=40

# Exclude thread counts below N from Phase 7. Equivalent to --min-threads.
# SWEEP_MIN_THREADS=8

# Exclude context sizes below N from Phase 7. Equivalent to --min-ctx.
# e.g. keep only 32k+ in the combination matrix:
# SWEEP_MIN_CTX=32768

# Exclude KV types below TYPE (quality order) from Phase 7. Equivalent to --min-ctk.
# e.g. keep only q8_0 and f16:
# SWEEP_MIN_CTK=q8_0

# Exclude batch sizes below N from Phase 7. Equivalent to --min-b.
# SWEEP_MIN_B=512

# Exclude ubatch sizes below N from Phase 7. Equivalent to --min-ub.
# SWEEP_MIN_UB=128
